pyred offers redmine module to run automatic action on redmine project hosting
server.

redmine can be run as a scripts
$ python src/redmine

or as python module after installation
$ python -m redmine

usage: redmine.py [-h] {upload,upload-issue,issue} ...

        redmine wrapper written in python with mechanize
        

positional arguments:
  {upload,upload-issue,issue}

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit


*issue*: create redmine issue

positional arguments:
  url                   url of the redmine server
  project               name of the redmine project
  {Support,Bug,Feature}
  subject
  description

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --login LOGIN
  --password PASSWORD
  --parent-issue PARENT_ISSUE
  --file-name FILE_NAME [FILE_NAME ...]
  --file-desc FILE_DESC [FILE_DESC ...]


*upload*: upload a file to redmine project

positional arguments:
  url                   url of the redmine server
  project               name of the redmine project
  file_name

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --login LOGIN
  --password PASSWORD
  --file-desc FILE_DESC [FILE_DESC ...]


*upload-issue*: upload a file to redmine issue

positional arguments:
  url                   url of the redmine server
  issue
  file_name

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --login LOGIN
  --password PASSWORD
  --file-desc FILE_DESC [FILE_DESC ...]
